No. —, original.

Ex parte Keogh. Submitted April 18, 1932. Decided April 25, 1932. Mr. John W. Keogh, pro se.

The petition for the issue of a writ of mandamus herein is denied for the want of jurisdiction. Luther v. Borden, 7 How. 1, 42; Pacific States Telephone & Telegraph Co. v. Oregon, 223 U. S. 118, 150; Marshall v. Dye, 231 U. S. 250, 256, 257; Massachusetts v. Mellon, 262 U. S. 447, 483, 488.
